1. Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place. 1. Whisk the egg, buttermilk and oil in a large bowl. 2. Whisk in the pancake mix until just combined. 3. Heat a large pan or griddle over medium heat and grease with butter or oil. 4. Pour about 1 tablespoon of the pancake mixture onto the griddle, making as many pancakes as will fit and cook for 2 minutes. 5. Flip the pancakes and cook for one minute longer and serve.